{{Infobox Organization | name = British Bryological Society | image = | image_border = | size = | caption = | formation = 1896<ref name="nhbs">{{cite web| url = http://www.nhbs.com/xchange/pages/xc155.html| archive-url = https://archive.is/20130130084645/http://www.nhbs.com/xchange/pages/xc155.html| dead-url = yes| archive-date = 2013-01-30| work = NHBS| title = British Bryological Society| accessdate = 2012-08-18}}</ref> | type = [[Learned society]] | headquarters = [[London]] | location = United Kingdom | membership = | language = English | leader_title = | leader_name = | key_people = | num_staff = | budget = | website = http://www.britishbryologicalsociety.org.uk/ }}
The '''British Bryological Society''' is an academic society dedicated to [[bryology]], which encourages the study of [[bryophyte]]s &ndash; [[moss]]es and [[Marchantiophyta|liverworts]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.museumwales.ac.uk/en/3109/| work= National Museum of Wales | title = British Bryological Society UK Catalogue of specimens | accessdate=2012-08-18 }}</ref> It publishes the peer-reviewed ''Journal of Bryology''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/maney/jbr | title =Journal of Bryology | work = Ingenta Connect | accessdate=2012-08-18 }}</ref>
