'''Duban''' is a [[Impact crater|crater]] in the northern hemisphere of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Duban was first seen in ''[[Voyager 2]]'' images, though the crater has also been seen in much higher resolution ''[[Cassini-Huygens Mission|Cassini]]'' images.  It is located at {{Coord|58.38|N|282.91|W|globe:enceladus}} and is 19&nbsp;kilometers across.<ref name=USGS>{{Gpn|1652|Duban}}</ref>  In the ''Cassini'' image, evidence for significant tectonic deformation can be seen along the northwest rim of the crater. 

[[Duban (disambiguation)|Duban]] is named after a sage who cured [[King Yunan]] of [[leprosy]] in ''[[Arabian Nights]]''.

