{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox settlement | official_name = Port-aux-Français | native_name = | other_name = | settlement_type = Village | image_skyline = Port aux Français.JPG | imagesize = 300px | image_caption = Port-aux-Français in 2004 | image_flag = | image_seal = | image_map = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = France Kerguelen#Indian Ocean | pushpin_map_caption = Location in [[Kerguelen Islands]] & [[Indian Ocean]] |pushpin_relief = yes | coordinates = {{coord|49.348653|S|70.219305|E|format=dms|region:AQ|display=inline,title}} | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = [[France]] | subdivision_type1 = [[Overseas territory (France)|Territory]] | subdivision_name1 = [[French Southern and Antarctic Lands]] (TAAF) | subdivision_type2 = District | subdivision_name2 = [[Kerguelen Islands]] | established_title = | established_date = | leader_title = | leader_name = | unit_pref = Imperial | area_total_km2 = | area_land_km2 = | elevation_footnotes = | elevation_m = | population_footnotes = | population_total = | population_as_of = | population_density_km2 = | timezone = | utc_offset = | postal_code_type = | postal_code = | area_code = | website = }}
'''Port-aux-Français''' is the capital settlement of the [[Kerguelen Islands]], [[French Southern and Antarctic Lands]], in the south [[Indian Ocean]]. The port station is located on the [[Gulf of Morbihan (Kerguelen)|Gulf of Morbihan]], at {{Coord|49.35|S|70.219|E}}.
==Research station== The station was selected in 1949 by the chief of mission [[Pierre Sicaud]] because of its sheltered position which was suitable for a runway that was never built. From 1955 to 1957, and using [[Australia]]n equipment, a French [[slaughterhouse]] company called Sidap constructed a [[seal hunting|sealing factory]]. The factory opened following the first marriage on the islands, that of Marc Pechenart and Martine Raulin on 16 December 1957. The factory closed in 1960, and the equipment was sent to [[Réunion]] in 2005. It has about 45 inhabitants in winter; the population can rise to more than 120 in summer.
Port-aux-Français has a shallow [[port|seaport]] and a [[quay]] for unloading supply ships, including the ''[[Marion Dufresne (1995)|Marion Dufresne]]''. The station, in addition to logistics necessary to its operation, consists of scientific laboratories ([[biology]], [[geophysics]]), technical installations ([[meteorology]], [[telecommunication]]s, satellite tracking, et cetera), a cinema and a small medical centre.
==Tidal gauges== The base of Port-aux-Français is equipped with a recently installed marigraphic station, having 3 measuring devices: * two [[tide gauges]] to measure pressure at sea bottom * a [[Wave radar|radar]] measuring the sea level. The two marigraphs and the radar send data to a local server, which relays them hourly to the Internet via the [[Argos System|Argos]] satellite system.
==Climate== Port-aux-Français has an ocean moderated [[Köppen climate classification#Group E: Polar and alpine (montane) climates|mild tundra climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification]] ''ET'').<ref name=Peel>{{cite journal | author=Peel, M. C. and Finlayson, B. L. and McMahon, T. A. | year=2007| title= Updated world map of the Köppen&ndash;Geiger climate classification | journal=Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci. | volume=11 | pages=1633–1644 |doi=10.5194/hess-11-1633-2007 | url=http://www.hydrol-earth-syst-sci.net/11/1633/2007/hess-11-1633-2007.pdf | issn = 1027-5606}}</ref> Temperatures (without windchill) tend to remain fairly stable throughout the year, rarely reaching over {{convert|18|C|F}} or falling below {{convert|-8|C|F}}.<ref name=weatherbase1>{{cite web | url = http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weatherall.php3?s=89916&units= | title = Weatherbase: Historical Weather for Port Aux Francais, France| publisher = Weatherbase | accessdate = February 28, 2013}}</ref> The average temperature in February, the warmest month, is {{convert|7.5|C|F}} with a maximum of {{convert|11.5|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|4.3|C|F}} during the night. In winter, August and July are the coldest months, averaging {{convert|4.8|to|5.0|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|-0.8|C|F}} at night.
Snowfall is possible in all months, even in summer though it is more common during the winter months than during the summer months. The climate is windier than in most places, with a recorded gust of {{cvt|80|m/s|km/h mph}}.<ref name= NOAA >{{cite web | url = ftp://ftp.atdd.noaa.gov/pub/GCOS/WMO-Normals/TABLES/REG__I/F1/61998.TXT | title = Climate Normals for Port Aux Francais 1961-1990 | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | accessdate = February 28, 2013}}</ref> The lowest recorded temperature was {{convert|-9.5|C|F}} on 11 August 2014, which beats the old record of {{convert|-9.4|C|F}} set in June 1953.<ref>http://www.ogimet.com/cgi-bin/gsynres?ind=61998&decoded=yes&ndays=2&ano=2014&mes=08&day=12&hora=00 </ref> The highest temperature was {{convert|23.0|C|F}} on 30 January 1959.<ref>http://docs.lib.noaa.gov/rescue/cd008A_pdf/0025873d.pdf </ref> {{Weather box | location = Port-aux-Français, Kerguelen Islands (1981–2010 averages, extremes 1950–present) | metric first = yes | single line = yes | Jan record high C = 25.8 | Feb record high C = 23.6 | Mar record high C = 22.3 | Apr record high C = 23.1 | May record high C = 16.8 | Jun record high C = 14.5 | Jul record high C = 13.2 | Aug record high C = 15.0 | Sep record high C = 15.8 | Oct record high C = 19.1 | Nov record high C = 19.9 | Dec record high C = 22.1 | year record high C = 25.8 | Jan high C = 11.9 | Feb high C = 12.2 | Mar high C = 11.1 | Apr high C = 9.4 | May high C = 7.1 | Jun high C = 5.4 | Jul high C = 5.1 | Aug high C = 5.2 | Sep high C = 5.8 | Oct high C = 7.4 | Nov high C = 9.1 | Dec high C = 10.9 | year high C = 8.4 | Jan mean C = 8.2 | Feb mean C = 8.4 | Mar mean C = 7.6 | Apr mean C = 6.1 | May mean C = 4.1 | Jun mean C = 2.7 | Jul mean C = 2.3 | Aug mean C = 2.3 | Sep mean C = 2.8 | Oct mean C = 4.0 | Nov mean C = 5.5 | Dec mean C = 7.2 | year mean C = 5.1 | Jan low C = 4.5 | Feb low C = 4.7 | Mar low C = 4.0 | Apr low C = 2.9 | May low C = 1.1 | Jun low C = 0.0 | Jul l